-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Donkey Kong Country 3.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--                    Donkey Kong Country 3: Dixie Kong's Double Trouble! (SNES)
--
-- STATUS: COMMUNITY world. location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED
-- from the official apworld worlds/dkc3 (Client.py game_watcher + Rom.py
-- location_rom_data + Locations.py + __init__.py, TheLX5/Archipelago @ branch
-- `dktoluca`, world_version 1.1.0, author PoryGone). The 220-entry location table
-- was GENERATED by PARSING Rom.py location_rom_data (ap_id → [wram_addr, bit,
-- optional invert]) with Python — not hand-copied — so every (AP id → offset/bit)
-- pair is exact. Mock-verified through MoonSharp against synthetic WRAM/CARTROM.
-- Loads crash-free on any ROM; self-disables on a non-AP cartridge.
--
-- SOURCE: https://github.com/TheLX5/Archipelago  (branch `dktoluca`, worlds/dkc3)
--         game string "Donkey Kong Country 3", patch_suffix ".apdkc3",
--         items_handling 0b111 (FULL remote), base ROM US 1.0
--         MD5 120abf304f0c40fe059f6a192ed4f947 (USHASH in worlds/dkc3/Rom.py).
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (SNI → BizHawk)  — see Research_V2/SNES_BRIDGE_2026-06-12.md
-- ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--   The dkc3 client is an SNIClient. Its SNI addresses translate to BizHawk SNES
--   memory domains. DKC3 reads almost everything from WRAM, plus the ROM header
--   for identity:
--     SNI WRAM_START(0xF50000)+off → domain "WRAM",   offset off  (= $7E0000+off)
--     SNI ROM_START(0x000000)+off  → domain "CARTROM", offset off  (raw ROM file
--                                    offset. Fallbacks "ROM"/"System Bus")
--   DKC3 is a LoROM cartridge. The client's identity read is
--   DKC3_ROMHASH_START = 0x7FC0 (the LoROM internal-header title region), and the
--   AP patch writes the ROM name there (patch.write_bytes(0x7FC0, "D3...")). So
--   this module reads the signature from CARTROM file offset 0x7FC0 and requires
--   the first two bytes to be "D3" — exactly validate_rom's `rom_name[:2] != b"D3"`
--   gate. (validate_rom also rejects an all-zero hash; a real "D3" prefix already
--   excludes that.)
--
--   The client reads (Client.py), and this module mirrors:
--     • save_file_name = Read(WRAM+0x5D9, 0x5) → WRAM. "No save loaded" when
--       byte[0]==0x00 OR the 5 bytes are all 0x55 (uninitialised). game_watcher
--       early-returns in that case; we gate detection on the same condition.
--     • location_ram_data = Read(WRAM+0x5FE, 0x81) → WRAM. ONE contiguous 129-byte
--       progress-flag block at $7E05FE..$7E067E that backs EVERY location. Each
--       location is {wram_addr in [0x5FE,0x67F), bit, optional invert}:
--           data        = location_ram_data[wram_addr - 0x5FE]
--           masked      = data & (1 << bit)
--           bit_set     = masked ~= 0
--           invert_bit  = (#entry >= 3) and entry[3]    -- only some Brothers Bear
--           checked when bit_set ~= invert_bit
--       (No active uncommented location uses invert in 1.1.0 — the Brothers Bear
--       trade-sequence entries that did are disabled — but the invert path is
--       implemented for forward-compat and to match game_watcher byte-for-byte.)
--   IDENTITY / VALIDATION (mirrors validate_rom + the game_watcher re-checks):
--     ROM header at CARTROM 0x7FC0 begins with "D3", AND a save file is loaded
--     (save_file_name gate). The AP patch bakes the "D3<ver>_<player>_<seed>" name
--     into the header at generation time.
--
-- HOW DKC3 CHECKS WORK (mirrors Client.py game_watcher)
--   game_watcher reads the single 0x81-byte flag block once, then for every
--   location not already checked computes data & (1<<bit) and reports it when
--   bit_set ~= invert_bit. There are NO in-map / brightness / settings gates in
--   the dkc3 client (unlike dkc2): a flag is either set or not. The only gate is
--   "a save file is loaded" (and it stays loaded — game_watcher re-reads the save
--   name afterwards and the ROM hash, and bails if either changed; we mirror the
--   save re-read each poll via the same gate). "Non-included" locations are simply
--   never in the server's location set, so gating poll() to ctx.locations (the
--   server's set) reproduces the client's effective behaviour. The client's
--   separate "Handle Collected Locations" RAM-backfill block (writing flags for
--   already-collected co-op locations, and the level-unlock propagation) is a
--   WRITE-side convenience that does NOT affect which checks WE detect, so it is
--   intentionally not mirrored here (we never write).
--
-- GOAL (mirrors __init__.py victory placement + game_watcher CLIENT_GOAL)
--   DKC3 has two goals (Options.Goal):
--     • knautilus (0)         : Victory item is locked at the `kastle_kaos`
--                               location (ap id 0xDC30A7 → WRAM 0x655 bit 1).
--     • banana_bird_hunt (1)  : Victory item is locked at the `banana_bird_mother`
--                               location (ap id 0xDC30B6 → WRAM 0x5FE bit 4).
--   In the official client the goal completes when the server hands the player the
--   Victory item (0xDC3000) back — but that item only exists because the player
--   physically reached the goal location, which sets exactly that location's RAM
--   flag. So the faithful, memory-readable goal signal is: the goal location's bit
--   is set. We read BOTH carrier bits; completion is reached when EITHER is set
--   (a player can only ever reach their own seed's goal location, so detecting
--   either is correct without needing slot_data — and if config.goal is provided
--   we honour it to match the exact carrier). This is the same RAM transition the
--   client's victory item is downstream of.
--
-- WHAT THIS DOES
--   • poll(): the game_watcher flag scan above → AP location ids, gated to the
--     slot's server location set and to "a save file is loaded".
--   • is_goal_complete(): true once the goal-carrier RAM bit is set (see GOAL).
--   • receive_item(): NO-OP (documented). items_handling = 0b111 (FULL remote) —
--     the dkc3 client owns ALL item delivery via an intricate, heavily-state-gated
--     set of WRAM writes (a recv-index handshake at DKC3_RECV_PROGRESS_ADDR; per-
--     item count increments at item_rom_data WRAM offsets; special Bear/Swanky/
--     Boomer coin-display pokes gated on the live current-level bytes; the Patch &
--     Skis progressive-boat upgrade state machine touching the inventory + per-
--     world progress words; and the Victory CLIENT_GOAL trigger). That delivery
--     path is the one piece that needs in-emulator verification before it is wired,
--     so it is left out rather than shipped unverified (a wrong write would corrupt
--     the save or desync the recv-index). Checks + goal above are fully functional
--     regardless.
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

local M = {}
M.name = "Donkey Kong Country 3"

local ADDRESSES_VERIFIED = true   -- table generated from worlds/dkc3 source

-- ── Memory domains ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
local WRAM    = "WRAM"
local CARTROM = "CARTROM"     -- SNES cartridge ROM in BizHawk; fallbacks below

-- ── Addresses / constants (worlds/dkc3 Client.py + Rom.py) ────────────────────
-- Expressed as BizHawk-domain offsets (already net of WRAM_START / ROM_START).
local SAVE_NAME_OFF   = 0x5D9     -- WRAM: 5-byte save-file name; 0x00 / all-0x55 = none
local SAVE_NAME_LEN   = 0x05
local FLAGS_BASE_OFF  = 0x5FE     -- WRAM: base of the single 0x81-byte flag block
local FLAGS_LEN       = 0x81      -- 129 bytes ($7E05FE..$7E067E inclusive)
local ROMHASH_OFF     = 0x7FC0    -- CARTROM: LoROM header title; first 2 = "D3"

-- Save-name sentinels (Client.py game_watcher / validate_rom).
local SAVE_EMPTY_BYTE = 0x00      -- name[0] == 0x00 → no save
local SAVE_UNINIT     = 0x55      -- name == 0x55 * 5 → uninitialised slot

-- Goal carriers (ap id → flag block offset & bit). See GOAL header block.
--   knautilus        : kastle_kaos        0xDC30A7 = [0x655, 1] → off 0x57, bit 1
--   banana_bird_hunt : banana_bird_mother 0xDC30B6 = [0x5FE, 4] → off 0x00, bit 4
local GOAL_KNAUTILUS_OFF, GOAL_KNAUTILUS_BIT = 0x655 - FLAGS_BASE_OFF, 1
local GOAL_BBHUNT_OFF,    GOAL_BBHUNT_BIT    = 0x5FE - FLAGS_BASE_OFF, 4

-- Option value (Options.Goal): which carrier is THIS seed's goal. Honoured when
-- config.goal is provided; otherwise EITHER carrier completes (see header).
local GOAL_OPT_KNAUTILUS  = 0
local GOAL_OPT_BBHUNT     = 1
local selected_goal       = nil   -- nil = unknown → accept either carrier

